      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah that makes sense. i also noticed some of the gaps in the data are just... weird. like there are these pockets of land where the population just disappears for a few years and then reappears later, but there aren't really any records of mass deaths or wars in those specific spots. it almost looks like they just moved underground or something. do you think there are other things that could cause these kinds of \"missing\" populations?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
